-CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets
-used to format a markup language
-add styles to HTML without changing HTML
-adding <style></style>element inbetween head tags
-we are not editing content, its just for visual satisfaction
-all css codes goes inside style attribute for reference 
-file needs to be saved as html file
-select element goes inside style, no need to enter <> (angle bracket) 
-need open and closing squiggly bracket {} for content inside selected element
-styles are called properties
-semi colon gives a break in between commands, meaning browser is ready to move on to the next styling command


<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
h1 {

background-color: (specify color);    (changing background color) 

}
</style>
</head>
<h1> enter title </h1>
<p> enter paragraph </p>
<h2> enter smaller title </h2>
<p> enter another paragraph </p>
</body>
</html>
